Class PodcastLocation

java.lang.Object
com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.module.podcast.PodcastLocation
public class PodcastLocation extends Object
Represents a podcast location, describing either the editorial focus or the source of production for a podcast's content. This class answers either "where is this podcast about?" or "where was the podcast made?".

  • Method Details

    • getLocation

      public String getLocation()
      Gets the human-readable location string. This is a free-form string that may conform to conventional location verbiage (e.g., "Austin, TX"), but should not be depended on to be parseable in any specific way.
      Returns:
      the location string, intended as a display value

    • setLocation

      public void setLocation(String location)
      Sets the human-readable location string. The value should not exceed 128 characters as it may be truncated by aggregators.
      Parameters:
      location - the location string to set

    • getRel

      public Optional<String> getRel()
      Gets the relationship type of the location.
      Returns:
      Optional containing either "subject" (default, content focus) or "creator" (production location)

    • setRel

      public void setRel(String rel)
      Sets the relationship type of the location.
      Parameters:
      rel - either "subject" (content focus) or "creator" (production location)

    • getGeo

      public Optional<String> getGeo()
      Gets the geographical coordinates in geoURI format.
      Returns:
      Optional containing the geoURI (RFC5870) formatted string (e.g., "geo:30.2672,97.7431")

    • setGeo

      public void setGeo(String geo)
      Sets the geographical coordinates in geoURI format.
      Parameters:
      geo - the geoURI (RFC5870) formatted string

    • getOsm

      public Optional<String> getOsm()
      Gets the OpenStreetMap identifier.
      Returns:
      Optional containing the OSM identifier (e.g., "R113314")

    • setOsm

      public void setOsm(String osm)
      Sets the OpenStreetMap identifier. The format should be the first character of OSM object type (Node, Way, Relation) followed by the ID.
      Parameters:
      osm - the OpenStreetMap identifier
